My constant advice to professional artists is to set aside a little time, each day if you can, to work on your online presence. If you combine that with consistent art output, it pays off exponentially later on when your audience grows. And it will if you put in the work!

twitter is still an essential tool for artists FOR NOW, but at the rate they're demoting independent artists' attempts to make a living, I'd strongly encourage ppl not to keep all their eggs in one basket and maintain at least one other art presence, at least for a static gallery

Not saying DA should be in anybody else's top places to post, I do it mostly out of nostalgia & familiarity from my days as a younger artist. But it's good to have an order of operations for posting your art, and it's good to update it periodically with what gets results

I've also started periodically updating my deviantart gallery https://t.co/PZ83bKpRp6, with each post linking to my other art / social media - I've actually gotten a couple adopts sold this way that didn't get picked up elsewhere! It's worth a little bit of time sometimes.

As mad as i constantly am at FA for their inexcusably awful moderation, my partner and i do pretty consistently find takers for our comms when we need em if we put time into maintaining our galleries, which gets us through dry spells when twitter decides to bury our posts.

Seeing other artists struggling with numbers & getting their commission posts buried on twitter is tough on morale, but I encourage everybody to keep posting your stuff on at least one other site, like furaffinity - sometimes not having to deal with an algorithm helps visibility!

taking today to tidy up our house after leaving in a rush and just chill with our cats, they missed us a ton, massive thanks to some local friends who loaned us a car all week and fed & played with our cats in shifts and watered our billion plants

so much for keeping it all in a tidy journal, i'm still kinda feeling things out. suffice it to say, i'm not going to let the emotional investments he made in me from one artist to another go to waste.

There's so, so much more I could say about the impact he had on my life just by being such a wonderful person. Their family took us on a month-long trip to Vietnam in November 2019, we got back right before covid hit. I'm trying to focus on all the forward momentum he gave me.

We got some help from family on our rent, just got a few other bills to clear. If you want to throw either of us a few bucks as we process things, my ko-fi is https://t.co/3be9MaN75R, theirs is https://t.co/nmOeVtdeNw . I'll forward them any condolences periodically too.

I might be a little sloppy getting back to people promptly as I'm trying to limit how much time I spend on social media in order to focus on my partner, and to actually concentrate on getting work done, but I'll be sure to update everybody who wants updates.

If i need more time I'll take it, and I'll do right by everybody waiting on commissions from me. If ppl want refunds I'll do adopts to get the money, if ppl want to give me deadlines for how much longer they're willing to wait I'm happy to work around those too.

We've still got a lot of grieving to do, as we spent the last week mostly focusing on their family. I'm happy to be home with a renewed appreciation for doing what I love, as he was very supportive of us as freelance artists. He inspired me so much over the 7 years I knew him.

In short, my partner's dad suddenly passed away the day after father's day. I was lucky enough to have texted him the night before to tell him how much he meant to me as a father figure & hear him reaffirm how glad he's been seeing us together, that's brought us a lot of peace.

We're finally back home, it's been a rough time but I'm eager to get back to work. I wrote about what happened last week in a bit more length on my FA journal, TW for a death in the family. https://t.co/USO3Zoo9me
Finally heading home tonight!

Had to trave out of state in a hurry yesterday for a family emergency, might be a few days before I'm back on the grid, my apologies to ppl I promised stuff for sooner... I should be able to continue working after this weekend.
